<p>
  If you or your company benefits from Rust and its ecosystem consider
  supporting it. There are many ways to support Rust:
</p>

<ul>
  <li>Contribute code.</li>
  <li>Write documentation.</li>
  <li>Publish blog posts, videos, or podcasts.</li>
  <li>
    Answer questions on
    <a href="https://users.rust-lang.org/">the forum</a>,
    <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/unanswered/tagged/rust">Stack Overflow</a>,
    <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/rust">Reddit</a>,
    <a href="https://matrix.to/#/#rust:matrix.org">Matrix</a>,
    or <a href="https://discord.gg/rust-lang">Discord</a>.
  </li>
  <li>Financial contribution.</li>
</ul>

<p>
  Open source has a bit of a problem with sustainability and burning people
  out. Paying people is one way that we can help compensate them for their time
  and make open source more sustainable.
</p>

<p>
  Below are people and projects contributing to the Rust ecosystem that are
  accepting financial contributions. If you or your company is able, consider
  supporting one or more of these fine folks in their work making Rust better.
  See also <a href="http://aturon.github.io/sponsor">Aaron Turon's list</a>.
</p>

<p>
  To add to, or update this list
  <a href="https://github.com/wezm/read-rust/issues/new?labels=support-rust&amp;template=support_rust.md">please raise an issue</a>.
</p>

